  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/apart-but-still-one,Elder Joni L. Koch,4,"In June 1994, I was anxiously driving back home from work to watch on TV our national soccer team play in the World Cup. Soon after I started my journey, I saw from afar on the sidewalk a man quickly moving forward in a wheelchair, which I noticed was decorated with our Brazilian flag. I knew then he was also going home to watch the game!"
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/apart-but-still-one,Elder Joni L. Koch,5,"When our paths crossed and our eyes met, for a fraction of a second, I felt strongly united with that man! We were going in different directions, didn’t know each other, and had clearly different social and physical conditions, but our same passion for soccer and love for our country made us feel like one in that very moment! I haven’t seen that man since then, but today, decades later, I can still see those eyes and feel that strong connection with that man. After all, we won the game and the World Cup that year!"
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/apart-but-still-one,Elder Joni L. Koch,6,"In the Church, in spite of our differences, the Lord expects us to be one! He said in the Doctrine and Covenants, “Be one; and if ye are not one ye are not mine.”"
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/apart-but-still-one,Elder Joni L. Koch,7,"As we all enter a meetinghouse to worship as a group, we should leave behind our differences, including race, social status, political preferences, and academic and professional achievements, and instead concentrate on our common spiritual objectives. Together we sing hymns, ponder about the same covenants during the sacrament, and say simultaneously an audible “amen” after talks, lessons, and prayers—meaning that we jointly agree with what was shared."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/apart-but-still-one,Elder Joni L. Koch,8,These things that we do collectively help create a strong sense of oneness within the congregation.
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/apart-but-still-one,Elder Joni L. Koch,9,"However, what really determines, solidifies, or destroys our unity is how we act when we are apart from our Church members. As we all know, it is inevitable and normal that eventually we will talk about each other."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/apart-but-still-one,Elder Joni L. Koch,10,"Depending on what we choose to say about one another, our words will either have our “hearts knit together in unity,”as Alma taught those he baptized in the Waters of Mormon, or they will erode the love, trust, and goodwill that should exist among us."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/apart-but-still-one,Elder Joni L. Koch,11,"There are comments that subtly destroy unity, such as “Yes, he’s a good bishop; oh, but you should have seen him when he was a young man!”"
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/apart-but-still-one,Elder Joni L. Koch,12,"A more constructive version of this might be “The bishop is so good, and he has grown so much in maturity and wisdom over the years.”"
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/apart-but-still-one,Elder Joni L. Koch,13,"Oftentimes we put permanent labels on people by saying something like “Our Relief Society president is a lost cause; she is so stubborn!” In contrast, we might say, “The Relief Society president has been less flexible lately; maybe she’s going through some difficult times. Let’s help her and sustain her!”"
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/apart-but-still-one,Elder Joni L. Koch,14,"Brothers and sisters, we have no right to portray anybody, including from our Church circle, as a badly finished product! Rather, our words about our fellow beings shouldreflect our belief in Jesus Christ and His Atonement and that, in Him and through Him, we can always change for the better!"
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/apart-but-still-one,Elder Joni L. Koch,15,Some start criticizing and becoming divided from Church leaders and members for things that are so small.
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/apart-but-still-one,Elder Joni L. Koch,16,"Such was the case of a man called Simonds Ryder, who became a member of the Church in 1831. After reading a revelation that pertained to him, he was perplexed to see that his name was misspelledRider,with the letteriinstead of with the lettery.His reaction to this event contributed to his questioning the prophet and eventually led to persecuting Joseph and falling away from the Church."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/apart-but-still-one,Elder Joni L. Koch,17,"It is also likely that we will all experience some correction from our ecclesiastical leaders, which will be a test of how united we are with them."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/apart-but-still-one,Elder Joni L. Koch,18,"I was only 11, but I remember that 44 years ago, the meetinghouse where my family attended church was to experience major remodeling. Before that undertaking began, there was a meeting in which local leaders and area leaders were discussing how the members would participate with labor in that effort. My father, who had previously presided over that unit for years, expressed his very strong opinion that this work should be done by a contractor and not by amateurs."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/apart-but-still-one,Elder Joni L. Koch,19,"Not only was his opinion rejected, but we heard that he was severely and publicly rebuked on that occasion. Now, this was a man who was very dedicated to the Church and had been a World War II soldier in Europe, used to resisting and fighting for what he believed in! One wondered what his reaction might be after this incident. Would he persist with his opinion and continue to oppose the decision already made?"
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/apart-but-still-one,Elder Joni L. Koch,20,We had seen families in our ward who had become weaker in the gospel and had stopped attending meetings because they could not be one with those who were leading. I myself also witnessed many of my friends from Primary not remaining faithful in their youth because their parents were always finding fault with those inside the Church.
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/apart-but-still-one,Elder Joni L. Koch,21,"My dad, however, decided to remain one with our fellow Saints. Some days later, when ward members were gathering to help in the construction, he “invited” our family to follow him to the meetinghouse, where we would make ourselves available to help in any way."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/apart-but-still-one,Elder Joni L. Koch,22,"I was furious. I felt like asking him, “Dad, why in the world are we going to help in the construction if you were against having the members do it?” But the look on his face discouraged me from doing that. I wanted to be well for the rededication. So, fortunately, I decided to be quiet and just go and help in the building!"
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/apart-but-still-one,Elder Joni L. Koch,23,"Father did not get to see the new chapel, as he passed away before the conclusion of this work. But we in the family, led now by my mom, continued doing our part until it was finished, and that kept us united with my father, with the Church members, with our leaders, and, most important, with the Lord!"
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/apart-but-still-one,Elder Joni L. Koch,24,"Just moments before His excruciating experiences in Gethsemane, when Jesus was praying to the Father for His Apostles and all of us, the Saints, He said, “That they all may be one; as thou, Father, art in me, and I in thee.”"
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/apart-but-still-one,Elder Joni L. Koch,25,"Brothers and sisters, I testify that as we decide to be one with the members and leaders of the Church—both when we’re assembled together and especially when we are apart—we will also feel more perfectly united with our Heavenly Father and the Savior. In the name of Jesus Christ, amen."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/apart-but-still-one,Elder Joni L. Koch,26,Notes
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/apart-but-still-one,Elder Joni L. Koch,27,"Doctrine and Covenants 38:27."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/apart-but-still-one,Elder Joni L. Koch,28,"Mosiah 18:21."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/apart-but-still-one,Elder Joni L. Koch,29,"See Milton V. Backman Jr.,The Heavens Resound: A History of the Latter-day Saints in Ohio, 1830–1838(1983), 93–94."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/apart-but-still-one,Elder Joni L. Koch,30,"John 17:21."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/a-yearning-for-home,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,4,"Recently, as we met with President Thomas S. Monson, he expressed, with great solemnity and a countenance of happiness, how much he loves the Lord and that he knows that the Lord loves him. My dear brothers and sisters, I know that President Monson is very grateful for your love, your prayers, and your dedication to the Lord and His great gospel."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/a-yearning-for-home,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,5,"Nearly a century ago, a family from Oregon was vacationing in Indiana—over 2,000 miles (3,200 km) away—when they lost their beloved dog, Bobbie. The frantic family searched for the dog everywhere but to no avail. Bobbie could not be found."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/a-yearning-for-home,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,6,"Heartbroken, they made the trip home, each mile taking them farther away from their cherished pet."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/a-yearning-for-home,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,7,"Six months later, the family was stunned to find Bobbie on their doorstep in Oregon. “Mangy, scrawny, feet worn to the bone—[he] appeared to have walked the entire distance … by himself.”Bobbie’s story captured the imagination of people across the United States, and he became known as Bobbie the Wonder Dog."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/a-yearning-for-home,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,8,"Bobbie is not the only animal who has baffled scientists with an amazing sense of direction and instinct for home. Some monarch butterfly populations migrate 3,000 miles (4,800 km) each year to climes better suited for their survival. Leatherback turtles travel across the Pacific Ocean from Indonesia to the coasts of California. Humpback whales swim from the cold waters of the North and South Poles toward the equator and back. Perhaps even more incredibly, the arctic tern flies from the Arctic Circle to Antarctica and back every year, some 60,000 miles (97,000 km)."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/a-yearning-for-home,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,9,"When scientists study this fascinating behavior, they ask questions such as “How do they know where to go?” and “How does each successive generation learn this behavior?”"
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/a-yearning-for-home,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,10,"When I read of this powerful instinct in animals, I can’t help but wonder, “Is it possible that human beings have a similar yearning—an inner guidance system, if you will—that draws them to theirheavenly home?”"
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/a-yearning-for-home,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,11,"I believe that every man, woman, and child has felt the call of heaven at some point in his or her life. Deep within us is a longing to somehow reach past the veil and embrace Heavenly Parents we once knew and cherished."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/a-yearning-for-home,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,12,Some might suppress this yearning and deaden their souls to its call. But those who do not quench this light within themselves can embark on an incredible journey—a wondrous migration toward heavenly climes.
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/a-yearning-for-home,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,13,"The sublime message of The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints is that God is our Father, that He cares about us, and that there is a way to return to Him."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/a-yearning-for-home,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,14,God calls to you.
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/a-yearning-for-home,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,15,"God knows your every thought, your sorrows, and your greatest hopes. God knows the many times you have sought Him. The many times you have felt limitless joy. The many times you have wept in loneliness. The many times you have felt helpless, confused, or angry."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/a-yearning-for-home,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,16,"Yet, no matter your history—if you have faltered, failed, feel broken, bitter, betrayed, or beaten—know that you are not alone. God still calls to you."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/a-yearning-for-home,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,17,"The Savior extends His hand to you. And, as He did to those fishermen who stood long ago on the banks of the Sea of Galilee, with infinite love He speaks to you: “Come, follow me.”"
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/a-yearning-for-home,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,18,"If you will hear Him, He will speak to you this very day."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/a-yearning-for-home,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,19,When you walk the path of discipleship—when you move toward Heavenly Father—there is something within you that will confirm that you have heard the call of the Savior and set your heart toward the light. It will tell you that you are on the right path and that you are returning home.
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/a-yearning-for-home,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,20,"Since the beginning of time, God’s prophets have urged the people of their day to “hearken unto the voice of the Lord thy God, … keep his commandments and his statutes … , [and] turn unto [Him] with all thine heart, and with all thy soul.”"
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/a-yearning-for-home,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,21,The scriptures teach us a thousand reasons why we should do this.
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/a-yearning-for-home,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,22,"Today, let me offer two reasons why we should turn to the Lord."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/a-yearning-for-home,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,23,"First, your life will be better."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/a-yearning-for-home,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,24,"Second, God will use you to make the lives of others better."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/a-yearning-for-home,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,25,"I testify that when we embark upon or continue the incredible journey that leads to God, our lives will be better."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/a-yearning-for-home,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,26,"This does not mean that our lives will be free from sorrow. We all know of faithful followers of Christ who suffer tragedy and injustice—Jesus Christ Himself suffered more than anyone. Just as God makes the “sun to rise on the evil and on the good,” He also allows adversity to test the just and the unjust.In fact, sometimes it seems that our lives are more difficultbecausewe are trying to live our faith."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/a-yearning-for-home,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,27,"No, following the Savior will not remove all of your trials. However, it will remove the barriers between you and the help your Heavenly Father wants to give you. God will be with you. He will direct your steps. He will walk beside you and even carry you when your need is greatest."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/a-yearning-for-home,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,28,"You will experience the sublime fruit of the Spirit: “love, joy, peace, longsuffering, gentleness, goodness, [and] faith.”"
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/a-yearning-for-home,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,29,"These spiritual fruits are not a product of temporal prosperity, success, or good fortune. They come from following the Savior, and they can be our faithful attendants even in the midst of the darkest storms."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/a-yearning-for-home,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,30,"The fires and tumults of mortal life may threaten and frighten, but those who incline their hearts to God will be encircled by His peace. Their joy will not be diminished. They will not be abandoned or forgotten."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/a-yearning-for-home,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,31,"“Trust in the Lord with all thine heart,” the scriptures teach, “and lean not unto thine own understanding. In all thy ways acknowledge him, and he shall direct thy paths.”"
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/a-yearning-for-home,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,32,"Those who heed the inner call and seek God, those who pray, believe, and walk the path the Savior has prepared—even if they stumble along the path at times—receive the consoling assurance that “all things shall work together for [their] good.”"
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/a-yearning-for-home,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,33,For God “gives strength to the weary and increases the power of the weak.”
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/a-yearning-for-home,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,34,"“For though the righteous fall seven times, they rise again.”"
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/a-yearning-for-home,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,35,"And the Lord in His goodness asks:"
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/a-yearning-for-home,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,36,Do you want to experience abiding joy?
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/a-yearning-for-home,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,37,Do you yearn to feel within your heart the peace that passes understanding?
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/a-yearning-for-home,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,38,Then turn your soul toward the light.
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/a-yearning-for-home,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,39,Begin your own wonderful journey home.
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/a-yearning-for-home,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,40,"As you do so, your life will be better, happier, and more purposeful."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/a-yearning-for-home,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,41,"On your journey back to Heavenly Father you will soon realize that this journey isn’t just about focusing on your own life. No, this path inevitably leads you to become a blessing in the lives of God’s other children—your brothers and sisters. And the interesting thing about the journey is that as you serve God, and as you care for and help your fellowmen, you will see great progress in your own life, in ways you could never imagine."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/a-yearning-for-home,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,42,"Perhaps you don’t consider yourself all that useful; perhaps you don’t consider yourself a blessing in somebody’s life. Often, when we look at ourselves, we see only our limitations and deficiencies. We might think we have to be “more” of something for God to use us—more intelligent, more wealthy, more charismatic, more talented, more spiritual. Blessings will come not so much because of your abilities but because of your choices. And the God of the universe will work within and through you, magnifying your humble efforts for His purposes."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/a-yearning-for-home,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,43,"His work has always advanced on this important principle: “Out of small things proceedeth that which is great.”"
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/a-yearning-for-home,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,44,"When writing to the Saints in Corinth, the Apostle Paul observed that not many of them would be considered wise by worldly standards. But that didn’t matter, because “God hath chosen the weak things of the world to confound the things which are mighty.”"
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/a-yearning-for-home,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,45,"The history of God’s work is filled with people who considered themselves inadequate. But they humbly served, relying on the grace of God and His promise: “Their arm shall be my arm, and I will be their shield … , and they shall fight manfully for me; and … I [will] preserve them.”"
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/a-yearning-for-home,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,46,"This past summer our family had a wonderful opportunity to visit some early Church history sites in the eastern United States. In a special way, we relived the history of that time. People I had read so much about—people like Martin Harris, Oliver Cowdery, and Thomas B. Marsh—became more real to me as we walked where they walked and pondered the sacrifices they made to build the kingdom of God."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/a-yearning-for-home,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,47,"They had many great traits that allowed them to make significant contributions to the Restoration of the Church of Jesus Christ. But they were also human, weak, and fallible—just as you and I are. Some found themselves at variance with the Prophet Joseph Smith and fell away from the Church. Later, many of the same people had a change of heart, humbled themselves, and once again sought and found fellowship with the Saints."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/a-yearning-for-home,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,48,"We might have a tendency to judge these brethren and other members like them. We might say, “I would never have abandoned the Prophet Joseph.”"
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/a-yearning-for-home,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,49,"While that may be true, we don’t really know what it was like to live in that time, in those circumstances. No, they were not perfect, but how encouraging it is to know that God was able to use them anyway. He knew their strengths and weaknesses, and He gave them the extraordinary opportunity to contribute a verse or a melody to the glorious anthem of the Restoration."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/a-yearning-for-home,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,50,"How encouraging it is to know, thoughweare imperfect, if our hearts are turned to God, He will be generous and kind and use us for His purposes."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/a-yearning-for-home,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,51,Those who love and serve God and fellowmen and humbly and actively participate in His work will see wondrous things happen in their lives and in the lives of those they love.
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/a-yearning-for-home,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,52,Doors that seemed shut will open.
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/a-yearning-for-home,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,53,Angels will go before them and prepare the way.
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/a-yearning-for-home,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,54,"No matter your position in your community or in the Church, God will use you, if you are willing. He will magnify your righteous desires and turn the compassionate actions you sow into a bountiful harvest of goodness."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/a-yearning-for-home,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,55,"We are, each one of us, “strangers and pilgrims”in this world. In many ways, we are far from home. But that doesn’t mean we need to feel lost or alone."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/a-yearning-for-home,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,56,"Our beloved Father in Heaven has given us the Light of Christ. And deep within each one of us, a heavenly stirring urges us to turn our eyes and hearts to Him as we make the pilgrimage back to our celestial home."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/a-yearning-for-home,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,57,"This requires effort. You cannot get there without striving to learn of Him, understanding His instructions, earnestly applying them, and putting one foot in front of the other."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/a-yearning-for-home,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,58,"No, life is not a self-driving car. It is not an airplane on autopilot."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/a-yearning-for-home,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,59,You cannot just float in the waters of life and trust that the current will take you wherever you hope to be one day. Discipleship requires our willingness to swim upstream when needed.
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/a-yearning-for-home,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,60,"No one else is responsible for your personal journey. The Savior will help you and prepare the way before you, but the commitment to follow Him and keep His commandments must come from you. That is your sole burden, your sole privilege."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/a-yearning-for-home,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,61,This is your great adventure.
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/a-yearning-for-home,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,62,Please heed the call of your Savior.
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/a-yearning-for-home,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,63,Follow Him.
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/a-yearning-for-home,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,64,"The Lord has established The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints to help you in this commitment to serve God and fellowmen. Its purpose is to encourage, teach, lift, and inspire. This wonderful Church provides opportunities for you to exercise compassion, reach out to others, and renew and keep sacred covenants. It is designed to bless your life and improve your home, community, and nation."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/a-yearning-for-home,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,65,"Come, join with us and trust the Lord. Lend your talents to His wonderful work. Reach out, encourage, heal, and support all who desire to feel and heed the yearning for our supernal home. Let us join together in this glorious pilgrimage to heavenly climes."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/a-yearning-for-home,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,66,"The gospel is a transcendent message of hope, happiness, and joy. It is the pathway that leads us home."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/a-yearning-for-home,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,67,"As we embrace the gospel in faith and deed, each day and every hour, we will draw a little closer to our God. Our lives will be better, and the Lord will use us in remarkable ways to bless those around us and bring about His eternal purposes. Of this I testify and leave you my blessing in the sacred name of Jesus Christ, amen."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/a-yearning-for-home,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,68,Notes
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/a-yearning-for-home,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,69,"See Susan Stelljes, “Bobbie the Wonder Dog,”The Oregon Encyclopedia,oregonencyclopedia.org."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/a-yearning-for-home,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,70,"SeeMatthew 4:19;Luke 18:22."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/a-yearning-for-home,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,71,"Deuteronomy 30:10."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/a-yearning-for-home,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,72,"Matthew 5:45."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/a-yearning-for-home,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,73,"Galatians 5:22."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/a-yearning-for-home,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,74,"Proverbs 3:5–6."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/a-yearning-for-home,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,75,"Doctrine and Covenants 90:24."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/a-yearning-for-home,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,76,"Isaiah 40:29, New International Version."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/a-yearning-for-home,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,77,"Proverbs 24:16, New International Version."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/a-yearning-for-home,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,78,"SeePhilippians 4:7."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/a-yearning-for-home,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,79,"Doctrine and Covenants 64:33."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/a-yearning-for-home,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,80,"1 Corinthians 1:27."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/a-yearning-for-home,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,81,"Doctrine and Covenants 35:14."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/a-yearning-for-home,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,82,"Hebrews 11:13;1 Peter 2:11."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/bearers-of-heavenly-light,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,4,"An elderly man was standing in line at the post office to buy stamps at the service counter. A young woman noticed that he walked with difficulty and offered to show him how to buy stamps from a machine to save time. The elderly gentleman said, “Thank you, but I prefer waiting. The machine won’t ask me about my arthritis.”"
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/bearers-of-heavenly-light,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,5,Sometimes it helps to talk to someone who cares about our troubles.
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/bearers-of-heavenly-light,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,6,"Pain, sorrow, and illness are experiences we all share—the moments of mishap, misery, and misfortune can add up to a sizable memory on our soul’s own internal hard drive."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/bearers-of-heavenly-light,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,7,"When it comes to our physical well-being, we accept aging and illness as part of our mortal journey. We seek the counsel of professionals who understand the physical body. When we suffer from emotional distress or mental illness, we seek the help of experts who treat these kinds of ailments."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/bearers-of-heavenly-light,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,8,"Just as we face physical and emotional trials in this mortality, we also face spiritual challenges. Most of us have experienced times in our lives when our testimony burns brightly. We also may have experienced times when our Heavenly Father seems distant. There are times when we treasure the things of the Spirit with all our hearts. There may also be times when they appear less precious or of diminished significance."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/bearers-of-heavenly-light,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,9,Today I wish to speak of spiritual wellness—how we can find healing from stagnation and walk a path of vibrant spiritual health.
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/bearers-of-heavenly-light,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,10,"Sometimes spiritual illness comes as a result of sin or emotional wounds. Sometimes spiritual breakdowns come so gradually that we can scarcely tell what is happening. Like layers of sedimentary rock, spiritual pain and grief can build over time, weighing upon our spirits until it is almost too heavy to bear. For example, this can happen when our responsibilities at work, home, and church become so overwhelming that we lose sight of the joy of the gospel. We might even feel as though we have no more to give or that living the commandments of God is beyond our strength."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/bearers-of-heavenly-light,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,11,But just because spiritual trials are real does not mean that they are incurable.
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/bearers-of-heavenly-light,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,12,We can heal spiritually.
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/bearers-of-heavenly-light,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,13,"Even the deepest spiritual wounds—yes, even those that may appear to be incurable—can be healed."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/bearers-of-heavenly-light,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,14,"My dear friends, the healing power of Jesus Christ is not absent in our day."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/bearers-of-heavenly-light,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,15,"The Savior’s healing touch can transform lives in our day just as it did in His. If we will but have faith, He can take our hands, fill our souls with heavenly light and healing, and speak to us the blessed words, “Rise, take up thy bed, and walk.”"
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/bearers-of-heavenly-light,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,16,"Whatever causes our spiritual ailments, they all have one thing in common: the absence of divine light."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/bearers-of-heavenly-light,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,17,"Darkness reduces our ability to see clearly. It dims our vision of that which was at one time plain and clear. When we are in darkness, we are more likely to make poor choices because we cannot see dangers in our path. When we are in darkness, we are more likely to lose hope because we cannot see the peace and joythat await us if we just keep pressing forward."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/bearers-of-heavenly-light,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,18,"Light, on the other hand, allows us to see things as they really are. It allows us to discern between truth and error, between the vital and the trivial. When we are in the light, we can make righteous choices based on true principles. When we are in the light, we have “a perfect brightness of hope”because we can see our mortal trials from an eternal perspective."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/bearers-of-heavenly-light,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,19,We will find spiritual healing as we step away from the shadows of the world and into the everlasting Light of Christ.
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/bearers-of-heavenly-light,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,20,"The more we understand and apply the doctrinal concept of light, the more we can guard against spiritual sicknesses that afflict or trouble us on every side and hand, and the better we can serve as energetic, courageous, caring, and humble bearers of the holy priesthood—true servants and disciples of our beloved and eternal King."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/bearers-of-heavenly-light,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,21,"Jesus Christ said, “I am the light of the world: he that followeth me shall not walk in [the] darkness, but shall have the light of life.”"
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/bearers-of-heavenly-light,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,22,What does this mean?
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/bearers-of-heavenly-light,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,23,"Simply this: He who humbly follows Jesus Christ will experience and share in His light. And that light will grow until it eventually dispels even the most profound darkness."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/bearers-of-heavenly-light,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,24,"It means that there is a power, a strong influence, that emanates from the Savior. It proceeds “forth from the presence of God to fill the immensity of space.”Because this power enlightens, uplifts, and illuminates our lives, the scriptures often call it light, but it is also referred to as spirit and truth."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/bearers-of-heavenly-light,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,25,"In the Doctrine and Covenants we read, “The word of the Lord is truth, and whatsoever is truth is light, and whatsoever is light is Spirit, even the Spirit of Jesus Christ.”"
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/bearers-of-heavenly-light,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,26,"This profound insight—that light is spirit, which is truth, and that this light shines upon every soul who comes into the world—is as important as it is hopeful. The Light of Christ enlightens and saturates the souls of all who hearken to the voice of the Spirit."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/bearers-of-heavenly-light,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,27,The Light of Christ fills the universe.
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/bearers-of-heavenly-light,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,28,It fills the earth.
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/bearers-of-heavenly-light,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,29,And it can fill every heart.
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/bearers-of-heavenly-light,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,30,"“God is no respecter of persons.”His light is available to all—great or small, rich or poor, privileged or disadvantaged."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/bearers-of-heavenly-light,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,31,"If you open your mind and heart to receive the Light of Christ and humbly follow the Savior, you will receive more light. Line upon line, here a little and there a little, you will gather more light and truth into your souls until darkness has been banished from your life."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/bearers-of-heavenly-light,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,32,God will open your eyes.
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/bearers-of-heavenly-light,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,33,God will give you a new heart.
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/bearers-of-heavenly-light,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,34,"God’s love, light, and truth will cause dormant things to spring to life, and you will be reborn into a newness of life in Christ Jesus."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/bearers-of-heavenly-light,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,35,"The Lord has promised, “If your eye be single to my glory, your whole bodies shall be filled with light, and there shall be no darkness in you; and that body which is filled with light comprehendeth all things.”"
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/bearers-of-heavenly-light,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,36,This is the ultimate remedy for spiritual sickness. Darkness vanishes in the presence of light.
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/bearers-of-heavenly-light,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,37,"However, God will not force us to embrace His light."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/bearers-of-heavenly-light,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,38,"If we become comfortable with darkness, it is unlikely that our hearts will change."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/bearers-of-heavenly-light,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,39,"For change to take place, we need to actively let the light in."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/bearers-of-heavenly-light,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,40,"During my flights as an airline captain across our planet earth, I was always fascinated by the beauty and perfection of God’s creation. I found especially captivating the relationship between the earth and the sun. I consider it a profound object lesson of how darkness and light exist."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/bearers-of-heavenly-light,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,41,"As we all know, within every 24 hours night turns to day and day turns to night."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/bearers-of-heavenly-light,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,42,"So, then, what is night?"
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/bearers-of-heavenly-light,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,43,Night is nothing more than a shadow.
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/bearers-of-heavenly-light,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,44,"Even in the darkest of nights, the sun does not cease to radiate its light. It continues to shine as bright as ever. But half of the earth is in darkness."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/bearers-of-heavenly-light,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,45,The absence of light causes darkness.
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/bearers-of-heavenly-light,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,46,"When the darkness of night falls, we do not despair and worry that the sun is extinguished. We do not postulate that the sun is not there or is dead. Weunderstand that we are in a shadow, that the earth will continue to rotate, and that eventually the rays of the sun will reach us once again."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/bearers-of-heavenly-light,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,47,"Darkness is not an indication that there is no light. Most often, it simply means we’re not in the right place to receive the light. During the recent solar eclipse, many made great efforts to get into the narrow band of a shadow created by the moon in the middle of a bright sunny day."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/bearers-of-heavenly-light,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,48,"In a very similar way, spiritual light continually shines upon all of God’s creation. Satan will make every effort to create a shadow or get us into a shadow of our own making. He will coerce us to create our own eclipse; he will push us into the darkness of his cavern."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/bearers-of-heavenly-light,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,49,"Spiritual darkness can draw a veil of forgetfulness around even those who once walked in the light and rejoiced in the Lord. Nevertheless, even in moments of greatest darkness, God hears our humble petitions, as we pray, “Lord, I believe; help thou mine unbelief.”"
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/bearers-of-heavenly-light,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,50,"In the days of Alma there were many who struggled to accept spiritual things, and “because of their unbelief,” God’s light and truth could not enter their souls “and their hearts were hardened.”"
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/bearers-of-heavenly-light,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,51,"Brethren, it is up to us to be in the right place to see the divine light and truth of the gospel of Jesus Christ. Even when night has fallen and the world seems dark, we can choose to walk in Christ’s light, keep His commandments, and courageously testify of His reality and His greatness."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/bearers-of-heavenly-light,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,52,"As a bearer of God’s priesthood and as a disciple of Jesus Christ, you are a bearer of light. Keep doing the things that will nurture His divine light. “Hold up your light”and “let [it] shine before men”—not so that they will see and admire you, but “that they may see your good works, and glorify your Father which is in heaven.”"
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/bearers-of-heavenly-light,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,53,"My dear brothers, you are instruments in the hands of the Lord with the purpose of bringing light and healing to the souls of Heavenly Father’s children. Perhaps you do not feel qualified to heal those who are spiritually ill—certainly not any more than a post office employee is qualified to help with arthritis. Maybe you face spiritual challenges of your own. Nevertheless, the Lord has called you. He has given you authority and responsibility to reach out to those in need. He has endowed you with His sacred priesthood power to bring light into the darkness and uplift and bless God’s children. God has restored His Church and His precious gospel, “which healeth the wounded soul.”He has prepared the path to spiritual wellness, to find healing from stagnation and move toward vibrant spiritual health."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/bearers-of-heavenly-light,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,54,"Every time you turn your hearts to God in humble prayer, you experience His light. Every time you seek His word and will in the scriptures, the light grows in brightness. Every time you notice someone in need and sacrifice your own comfort to reach out in love, the light expands and swells. Every time you reject temptation and choose purity, every time you seek or extend forgiveness, every time you courageously testify of truth, the light chases away darkness and attracts others who are also seeking light and truth."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/bearers-of-heavenly-light,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,55,"Think about your own personal experiences, moments of service to God and fellowmen when divine light has shined in your life—in the holy temple, at the sacrament table, in a quiet moment of prayerful pondering, in your family gatherings, or during an act of priesthood service. Share those moments with family, friends, and especially with our youth, who are seeking light. They need to hear from you that with this light come hope and healing, even in a world full of darkness."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/bearers-of-heavenly-light,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,56,"Christ’s light brings hope, happiness, and healing of any spiritual wound orailment.Those who experience this refining influence become instruments in the hands of the Light of the World to give light to others.They will feel what King Lamoni felt: “This light had infused such joy into his soul, the cloud of darkness having been dispelled, and … the light of everlasting life was lit up in his soul.”"
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/bearers-of-heavenly-light,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,57,"My dear brethren, my dear friends, it is our quest to seek the Lord until His light of everlasting life burns brightly within us and our testimony becomes confident and strong even in the midst of darkness."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/bearers-of-heavenly-light,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,58,"It is my prayer and blessing that you will succeed in fulfilling your destiny as priesthood holders of Almighty God and always be joyful bearers of His heavenly light. In the sacred name of Jesus Christ, our Master, amen."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/bearers-of-heavenly-light,President Dieter F. Uchtdorf,59,Notes
