  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/the-book-of-mormon-what-would-your-life-be-like-without-it,President Russell M. Nelson,4,"In 1986, I was invited to give a special lecture at a university in Accra, Ghana. There I met a number of dignitaries, including an African tribal king. As we visited prior to the lecture, the king spoke to me only through his linguist, who then translated for me. I responded to the linguist, and the linguist then translated my responses to the king."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/the-book-of-mormon-what-would-your-life-be-like-without-it,President Russell M. Nelson,5,"After my lecture, the king made his way directly to me, but this time without his linguist. To my surprise, he spoke in perfect English—the Queen’s English, I might add!"
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/the-book-of-mormon-what-would-your-life-be-like-without-it,President Russell M. Nelson,6,The king seemed puzzled. “Just who are you?” he asked.
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/the-book-of-mormon-what-would-your-life-be-like-without-it,President Russell M. Nelson,7,"I replied, “I am an ordained Apostle of Jesus Christ.”"
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/the-book-of-mormon-what-would-your-life-be-like-without-it,President Russell M. Nelson,8,"The king asked, “What can you teach me about Jesus Christ?”"
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/the-book-of-mormon-what-would-your-life-be-like-without-it,President Russell M. Nelson,9,"I responded with a question: “May I ask what you already know about Him?”"
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/the-book-of-mormon-what-would-your-life-be-like-without-it,President Russell M. Nelson,10,The king’s response revealed he was a serious student of the Bible and one who loved the Lord.
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/the-book-of-mormon-what-would-your-life-be-like-without-it,President Russell M. Nelson,11,I then asked if he knew about the ministry of Jesus Christ to the people of ancient America.
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/the-book-of-mormon-what-would-your-life-be-like-without-it,President Russell M. Nelson,12,"As I expected, he did not."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/the-book-of-mormon-what-would-your-life-be-like-without-it,President Russell M. Nelson,13,"I explained that after the Savior’s Crucifixion and Resurrection, He came to the people of ancient America, where He taught His gospel. He organized His Church and asked His disciples to keep a record of His ministry among them."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/the-book-of-mormon-what-would-your-life-be-like-without-it,President Russell M. Nelson,14,"“That record,” I continued, “is what we know as the Book of Mormon. It is another testament of Jesus Christ. It is a companion scripture to the Holy Bible.”"
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/the-book-of-mormon-what-would-your-life-be-like-without-it,President Russell M. Nelson,15,"At this point, the king becameveryinterested. I turned to the mission president accompanying me and asked if he had an extra copy of the Book of Mormon with him. He pulled one from his briefcase."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/the-book-of-mormon-what-would-your-life-be-like-without-it,President Russell M. Nelson,16,"I opened it to3 Nephi chapter 11, and together the king and I read the Savior’s sermon to the Nephites. I then presented the copy of the Book of Mormon to him. His response lodged in my mind and heart forever: “Youcould have given me diamonds or rubies, but nothing is more precious to me than this additional knowledge about the Lord Jesus Christ.”"
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/the-book-of-mormon-what-would-your-life-be-like-without-it,President Russell M. Nelson,17,"After experiencing the power of the Savior’s words in 3 Nephi, the king proclaimed, “If I am converted and join the Church, I will bring my whole tribe with me.”"
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/the-book-of-mormon-what-would-your-life-be-like-without-it,President Russell M. Nelson,18,"“Oh, King,” I said, “it doesn’t work that way. Conversion is an individual matter. The Savior ministered to the Nephites one by one. Each individual receives a witness and testimony of the gospel of Jesus Christ.”"
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/the-book-of-mormon-what-would-your-life-be-like-without-it,President Russell M. Nelson,19,"My brothers and sisters, how preciousisthe Book of Mormon to you? If you were offered diamonds or rubiesorthe Book of Mormon, which would you choose? Honestly, whichisof greater worth to you?"
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/the-book-of-mormon-what-would-your-life-be-like-without-it,President Russell M. Nelson,20,"Remember in the Sunday morning session of the April 2017 general conference, President Thomas S. Monson pleaded with “each of us to prayerfully study and ponder the Book of Mormon each day.”Many have responded to our prophet’s plea."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/the-book-of-mormon-what-would-your-life-be-like-without-it,President Russell M. Nelson,21,Let me say that neither I nor eight-year-old Riley knew anyone was taking our pictures. Notice that Riley is reading his Book of Mormon with the help of an “I Am a Child of God” bookmark.
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/the-book-of-mormon-what-would-your-life-be-like-without-it,President Russell M. Nelson,22,Something powerful happens when a child of God seeks to know more about Him and His Beloved Son. Nowhere are those truths taught more clearly and powerfully than in the Book of Mormon.
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/the-book-of-mormon-what-would-your-life-be-like-without-it,President Russell M. Nelson,23,"Since President Monson’s challenge six months ago, I have tried to follow his counsel. Among other things, I’ve made lists of what the Book of Mormonis,what itaffirms,what itrefutes,what itfulfills,what itclarifies,and what itreveals.Looking at the Book of Mormon through these lenses has been an insightful and inspiring exercise! I recommend it to each of you."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/the-book-of-mormon-what-would-your-life-be-like-without-it,President Russell M. Nelson,24,"During these six months, I have invited various groups—including my Brethren in the Quorum of the Twelve, missionaries in Chile, and mission presidents and their wives gathered in Argentina—to consider three related questions that I urge you to think about today:"
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/the-book-of-mormon-what-would-your-life-be-like-without-it,President Russell M. Nelson,25,"First, what would your life be likewithoutthe Book of Mormon? Second, what would younot know? And third, what would younot have?"
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/the-book-of-mormon-what-would-your-life-be-like-without-it,President Russell M. Nelson,26,"Enthusiastic answers from these groups came straight from their hearts. Here are just a few of their comments:"
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/the-book-of-mormon-what-would-your-life-be-like-without-it,President Russell M. Nelson,27,"“Without the Book of Mormon, I would be confused about the conflicting teachings and opinions about somanythings. I would be just like I was before I found the Church, when I was searching for knowledge, faith, and hope.”"
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/the-book-of-mormon-what-would-your-life-be-like-without-it,President Russell M. Nelson,28,"Another said: “I would not know about the role the Holy Ghost can play in my life.”"
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/the-book-of-mormon-what-would-your-life-be-like-without-it,President Russell M. Nelson,29,"Another: “I would not clearly understand my purpose here on earth!”"
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/the-book-of-mormon-what-would-your-life-be-like-without-it,President Russell M. Nelson,30,"Another respondent said: “I would not know that there is continuing progress after this life. Because of the Book of Mormon, I know that there really islife after death. That is the ultimate goal for which we are working.”"
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/the-book-of-mormon-what-would-your-life-be-like-without-it,President Russell M. Nelson,31,"This last comment made me reflect on my life decades ago as a young surgical resident. One of the sobering responsibilities a surgeon bears, on occasion, is to inform the family when a loved one passes away. In one hospital where I worked, a special room was built with padded walls where family members could receive such news. There, some people manifested their grief by banging their heads against those padded walls. How I longed to teach those individuals that death, though difficult for surviving loved ones, is a necessary part of our immortal existence. Death allows us to progress to the next world."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/the-book-of-mormon-what-would-your-life-be-like-without-it,President Russell M. Nelson,32,"Another respondent to my question said: “I did not have a life until I read the Book of Mormon. Even though I had prayed and gone to my church all my life, the Book of Mormon helped me to really communicate with Heavenly Father for the first time.”"
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/the-book-of-mormon-what-would-your-life-be-like-without-it,President Russell M. Nelson,33,"Another said: “Without the Book of Mormon, I wouldn’t understand that the Savior not only suffered for my sins, but He can heal my pains and sorrows.”"
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/the-book-of-mormon-what-would-your-life-be-like-without-it,President Russell M. Nelson,34,"And yet another: “I would not know that we have prophets to lead us.”"
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/the-book-of-mormon-what-would-your-life-be-like-without-it,President Russell M. Nelson,35,"Immersing ourselves regularly in the truths of the Book of Mormon can be a life-changing experience. One of our missionary granddaughters, Sister Olivia Nelson, promised an investigator that if he would read the Book of Mormon daily, his test scores on his university exams would improve. He did, and they did."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/the-book-of-mormon-what-would-your-life-be-like-without-it,President Russell M. Nelson,36,"My dear brothers and sisters, I testify that the Book of Mormon is truly the word of God. It contains the answers to life’s most compelling questions. It teaches the doctrine of Christ.It expands and clarifies many of the “plain and precious”truths that were lost through centuries of time and numerous translations of the Bible."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/the-book-of-mormon-what-would-your-life-be-like-without-it,President Russell M. Nelson,37,The Book of Mormon provides the fullest and most authoritative understanding of the Atonement of Jesus Christ to be found anywhere. It teaches what it really means to be born again. From the Book of Mormon we learn about the gathering of scattered Israel. We know why we are here on earth. These and other truths are more powerfully and persuasively taught in the Book of Mormon than in any other book. The full power of the gospel of Jesus Christ is contained in the Book of Mormon. Period.
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/the-book-of-mormon-what-would-your-life-be-like-without-it,President Russell M. Nelson,38,The Book of Mormon both illuminates the teachings of the Master and exposes the tactics of the adversary.The Book of Mormon teaches true doctrine to dispel false religious traditions—such as the erroneous practice of performing infant baptisms.The Book of Mormon gives purpose to life by urging us to ponder the potential of eternal life and “never-ending happiness.”The Book of Mormon shatters the false beliefs that happiness can be found in wickednessand that individual goodness is all that is required to return to the presence of God.It abolishes forever the false concepts that revelation ended with the Bible and that the heavens are sealed today.
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/the-book-of-mormon-what-would-your-life-be-like-without-it,President Russell M. Nelson,39,"When I think of the Book of Mormon, I think of the wordpower.The truths of the Book of Mormon have thepowerto heal, comfort, restore, succor, strengthen, console, and cheer our souls."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/the-book-of-mormon-what-would-your-life-be-like-without-it,President Russell M. Nelson,40,"My dear brothers and sisters, I promise that as you prayerfully study the Book of Mormonevery day,you will make better decisions—every day.I promise that as you ponder whatyou study, the windows of heaven will open, and you will receive answers to your own questions and direction for your own life. I promise that as you daily immerse yourself in the Book of Mormon, you can be immunized against the evils of the day, even the gripping plague of pornography and other mind-numbing addictions."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/the-book-of-mormon-what-would-your-life-be-like-without-it,President Russell M. Nelson,41,"Whenever I hear anyone, including myself, say, “I know the Book of Mormon is true,” I want to exclaim, “That’s nice, but it is not enough!” We need to feel, deep in “the inmost part” of our hearts,that the Book of Mormonisunequivocally the word of God. We must feel it so deeply that we would never want to live even one day without it. I might paraphrase President Brigham Young in saying, “I wish I had the voice of seven thunders to wake up the people”to the truth and power of the Book of Mormon."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/the-book-of-mormon-what-would-your-life-be-like-without-it,President Russell M. Nelson,42,We need to be like this young missionary serving in Europe who felt so deeply about the truth of the Book of Mormon that he literally ran with a copy of this sacred record to the man in a park he and his companion had just found.
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/the-book-of-mormon-what-would-your-life-be-like-without-it,President Russell M. Nelson,43,"I testify that Joseph Smith was and istheprophet of this last dispensation. It was he who, through the gift and power of God, translated this holy book. This isthebook that will help to prepare the world for the Second Coming of the Lord."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/the-book-of-mormon-what-would-your-life-be-like-without-it,President Russell M. Nelson,44,"I testify that Jesus Christ is the literal and living Son of our living God. He is our Savior, our Redeemer, our great Exemplar, and our Advocate with the Father. He was the promised Messiah, the mortal Messiah, and will be the millennial Messiah. I testify with my whole soul that in a most miraculous and singular way, the Book of Mormon teaches us of Jesus Christ and His gospel."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/the-book-of-mormon-what-would-your-life-be-like-without-it,President Russell M. Nelson,45,"I know that President Thomas S. Monson is the prophet of God on the earth today. I love him and sustain him with all of my heart. I so testify in the sacred name of Jesus Christ, amen."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/the-book-of-mormon-what-would-your-life-be-like-without-it,President Russell M. Nelson,46,"The Book of Mormonis:"
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/the-book-of-mormon-what-would-your-life-be-like-without-it,President Russell M. Nelson,47,"Another testament of Jesus Christ. Its major writers—Nephi, Jacob, Mormon, Moroni—and its translator, Joseph Smith, werealleyewitnesses of the Lord."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/the-book-of-mormon-what-would-your-life-be-like-without-it,President Russell M. Nelson,48,A record of His ministry to people who lived in ancient America.
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/the-book-of-mormon-what-would-your-life-be-like-without-it,President Russell M. Nelson,49,"True, as attested by the Lord Himself."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/the-book-of-mormon-what-would-your-life-be-like-without-it,President Russell M. Nelson,50,"The Book of Mormonaffirms:"
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/the-book-of-mormon-what-would-your-life-be-like-without-it,President Russell M. Nelson,51,"The individual identity of Heavenly Father and His Beloved Son, Jesus Christ."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/the-book-of-mormon-what-would-your-life-be-like-without-it,President Russell M. Nelson,52,"The necessity of the Fall of Adam and the wisdom of Eve, that men might have joy."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/the-book-of-mormon-what-would-your-life-be-like-without-it,President Russell M. Nelson,53,"The Book of Mormonrefutesnotions that:"
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/the-book-of-mormon-what-would-your-life-be-like-without-it,President Russell M. Nelson,54,Revelation ended with the Bible.
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/the-book-of-mormon-what-would-your-life-be-like-without-it,President Russell M. Nelson,55,Infants need to be baptized.
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/the-book-of-mormon-what-would-your-life-be-like-without-it,President Russell M. Nelson,56,Happiness can be found in wickedness.
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/the-book-of-mormon-what-would-your-life-be-like-without-it,President Russell M. Nelson,57,Individual goodness is adequate for exaltation (ordinances and covenants are needed).
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/the-book-of-mormon-what-would-your-life-be-like-without-it,President Russell M. Nelson,58,The Fall of Adam tainted mankind with “original sin.”
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/the-book-of-mormon-what-would-your-life-be-like-without-it,President Russell M. Nelson,59,"The Book of Mormonfulfills biblical propheciesthat:"
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/the-book-of-mormon-what-would-your-life-be-like-without-it,President Russell M. Nelson,60,“Other sheep” shall hear His voice.
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/the-book-of-mormon-what-would-your-life-be-like-without-it,President Russell M. Nelson,61,"God will do “a marvelous work and a wonder,” speaking “out of the dust.”"
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/the-book-of-mormon-what-would-your-life-be-like-without-it,President Russell M. Nelson,62,The “stick of Judah” and the “stick of Joseph” will become one.
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/the-book-of-mormon-what-would-your-life-be-like-without-it,President Russell M. Nelson,63,Scattered Israel will be gathered “in the latter days” and how that will be done.
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/the-book-of-mormon-what-would-your-life-be-like-without-it,President Russell M. Nelson,64,The land of inheritance for the lineage of Joseph is the Western Hemisphere.
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/the-book-of-mormon-what-would-your-life-be-like-without-it,President Russell M. Nelson,65,"The Book of Mormonclarifiesunderstanding about:"
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/the-book-of-mormon-what-would-your-life-be-like-without-it,President Russell M. Nelson,66,Our premortal existence.
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/the-book-of-mormon-what-would-your-life-be-like-without-it,President Russell M. Nelson,67,Death. It is a necessary component of God’s great plan of happiness.
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/the-book-of-mormon-what-would-your-life-be-like-without-it,President Russell M. Nelson,68,"Postmortal existence, which begins in paradise."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/the-book-of-mormon-what-would-your-life-be-like-without-it,President Russell M. Nelson,69,"How the resurrection of the body, reunited with its spirit, becomes an immortal soul."
  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/the-book-of-mormon-what-would-your-life-be-like-without-it,President Russell M. Nelson,70,How our judgment by the Lord will be according to our deeds and the desires of our hearts.
