  2017,"10",/general-conference/2017/10/the-living-bread-which-came-down-from-heaven,Elder D. Todd Christofferson,51,"John 6:60, 66. It was on this occasion that the Savior asked His Twelve, “Will ye also go away?” (John 6:67). Responding for the Twelve with resolute faith, Peter answered: “Lord, to whom shall we go? thou hast the words of eternal life. And we believe and are sure that thou art that Christ, the Son of the living God” (John 6:68–69). I don’t know if, at that moment, Peter and his Brethren understood what the Lord was teaching any better than the disciples who were now abandoning the Master, but Peter did know by the certain witness of the Spirit that Jesus was the Christ, the Son of the living God (see alsoMatthew 16:15–17), and that salvation could be found nowhere else. He was therefore fully committed to follow Jesus regardless. If he had questions, they could be resolved in due course, but he would not be dissuaded from loyalty to the Son of God—setting a wonderful example for us all."
